The paper deals with the problem of rendezvous in cognitive radio networks, which is a topic related to networking and communication. Specifically, the paper proposes a new algorithm for anonymous rendezvous in heterogeneous cognitive radio networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT), as it discusses the expected time-to-rendezvous (ETTR) and maximum time-to-rendezvous (MTTR) of different algorithms. Additionally, the paper deals with cognitive radio networks (cs.CR) and distributed computing (cs.DC) as it proposes an algorithm that can be implemented in a symmetric, asynchronous, and heterogeneous setting with multiple radios. Finally, the paper involves systems and control (cs.SY) as it proposes a new algorithm for controlling the behavior of cognitive radio networks.
